Description: Discovered  by its close proximity (separation of 107.9â€³) to the SLACS lens SDSS J0737+3216 - the two lenses are at a common redshift. Danny's lensing galaxy is a large red elliptical, while the lensed source is blue, as expected for lens systems. The identified quad geometry is a typical lens geometry and may be called cusp dominated (e.g. Kochanek 2006), as it occurs when the source lies near to a cusp of the inner caustic.
Name: HST J073736.40+321540.3
